// HD Curve - Display (v2.23)
// Put this on the last node after any LUTs or grades you want to inspect.
// The chart samples the bottom row of the probe strip generated by the probe DCTL.
//
// v2.23 changes (on top of v2.22):
// - Centered text (legends, tick numbers, warning) is now truly centered:
//   the font's glyph ink sits ~2 units right of its advance box, which made
//   everything render slightly right of center (TEXT_INK_SHIFT).
// - Space character advance narrowed from 10 to 4 font units - fixes the
//   oversized gap in "Log Exp".
//
// v2.22 changes (on top of v2.21):
// - The slider is now "Grid Thickness" (default 2.2) and only affects the
//   grid and border. The RGB curves are fixed at factor 2.4
//   (CURVE_THICKNESS_FACTOR below).
//
// v2.21 changes (on top of v2.20):
// - Datasheet 1:1 now works with the X axis labeled in Stops too (stops are
//   converted to decades for the scaling; 1 stop = log10(2) decades). It
//   requires the Density Y axis - Output % is linear and has no fixed
//   log-unit size, so it falls back to Fill Width there.
// - Tooltips on all controls (requires Resolve 19.1+; ignored below that).
//
// v2.20 changes (on top of v2.19):
// - Isotropic 1:1 sizing is now an explicit Plot Shape option
//   ("Datasheet 1:1") instead of engaging silently in Fill Width. Fill
//   Width always fills the available area, so the plot no longer shrinks
//   when the density range grows (e.g. with Output Signal linearization).
//
// v2.19 changes (on top of v2.18):
// - "Output Signal" option for the Density Y axis. Density is
//   -log10(light), so the signal must be linearized through the display
//   EOTF for photometrically true density values and D-logE slopes:
//     None / Linear    - density straight off the code values (as before;
//                        also correct when the chain outputs linear light)
//     Video Gamma 2.4  - chain outputs Rec.709 / gamma 2.4 video
//     sRGB Monitor     - chain outputs sRGB
//   Default is None / Linear (identical to previous behavior). Output %,
//   curve shape, clip points and the active-range detection are unaffected.
//
// v2.18 changes (on top of v2.17):
// - Grid-to-curve thickness ratio raised to 2.2/2.4: at the default Line
//   Thickness of 2.4 the grid renders at factor 2.2, scaling proportionally
//   from there.
//
// v2.17 changes (on top of v2.16):
// - Grid lines track the curve thickness (80% of the RGB line width) in
//   every view, fullscreen included; the Line Thickness slider scales grid
//   and curves together.
//
// v2.16 changes (on top of v2.15):
// - Right Overlay grid lines track the curve thickness (80% of the RGB line
//   width) instead of the hairline UI-scale rule; fullscreen is unchanged.
//
// v2.15 changes (on top of v2.14):
// - "Show Grid" checkbox (default on). Off hides only the interior grid
//   lines; the plot border, mid gray line, tick numbers and legends stay.
//
// v2.14 changes (on top of v2.13):
// - Legends use the same color as the tick numbers, at 60% size, with the
//   gaps around them collapsed: the plot gets the vertical space back and
//   the numbers stay uncompressed.
//
// v2.13 changes (on top of v2.12):
// - Axis legends relocated: "Log Exp" is centered above the top numbers row,
//   "Stops" centered below the bottom numbers row. "Stops" now shows in
//   every X mode (the bottom numbers are always camera stops).
//
// v2.12 changes (on top of v2.11):
// - Plot border uses the same color as the grid, twice as thick (was a
//   brighter gray).
// - Grid lines never collapse below 3px (Right Overlay computed hairlines).
// - Log exposure mode: axis legends "Log Exp" (top row) and "Stops" (bottom
//   row) at the far left of the chart.
// - Fixed: with "Offset Exposure to 0" the stops axis "0" label could vanish
//   (offset used round instead of floor of the range top).
// - Fixed: Plot Shape "Square" now wins over the isotropic sensitometry
//   sizing in Fullscreen.
// - Removed "Linear Input" (X) and "Linear Output" (Y) axis options.
//
// v2.11 changes (on top of v2.10):
// - X Axis defaults to Log Exposure.
// - The plot is framed on all four sides: auto-scaled ranges do not always
//   end on a tick, so top/right edges no longer lose their grid line.
//
// v2.10 changes (on top of v2.9):
// - Active range detection uses separate thresholds for shadows and
//   highlights (ACTIVE_RANGE_THRESH_* below): the highlight shoulder
//   converges slowly in density, so it gets a finer threshold and is no
//   longer trimmed while the curve is still visibly rising.
// - "Offset Exposure to 0" (renamed) now also works on the Stops X axis:
//   labels shift so the range ends at 0 and counts down, for reading the
//   dynamic range directly. Pure relabeling - nothing else moves.
// - Density Y axis rounds up to the next 0.5 (not 0.25), so the grid line
//   above the black point is always visible.
// - Right Overlay keeps its square plot in sensitometry mode (isotropic 1:1
//   sizing is fullscreen-only).
//
// v2.9 changes (on top of v2.8):
// - Sensitometry layout for X = Log Exposure: log exposure labels on TOP of
//   the plot (integers in square views, one decimal otherwise), camera stops
//   along the bottom (every other integer; relative to the range top when
//   "Offset Log Exposure to 0" is on). Grid shows half-decade minor and
//   full-decade major lines.
// - With Y = Density as well, the plot is scaled isotropically (1:1 - one
//   density unit equals one log-exposure decade in pixels).
// - Density Y axis always adapts to the curve's actual black point (rounded
//   up to the next 0.25, min 0.5) instead of defaulting to 3.0 - most LUTs
//   sit around density 1.5-2.0 like scanned film.
//
// v2.8 changes (on top of v2.7):
// - Right Overlay is now a fixed analysis view: always a square plot on a
//   solid background, centered vertically in the chart area, and the whole
//   frame is scaled down into the remaining left area (letterboxed) so
//   nothing is hidden. Plot Shape and Transparent Background settings only
//   apply to Fullscreen; axis modes, encoding, line thickness, Clamp to
//   Active Range and Offset Log Exposure to 0 work in both views.
//
// v2.7 changes (on top of v2.6):
// - Active range detection reworked to match the proven Sensitometry Curve
//   Display implementation: the scan runs in density space with a
//   per-channel relative threshold against the plateau values, taking the
//   widest union across R/G/B. This makes "Clamp to Active Range" actually
//   bite (the old absolute linear threshold saw almost everything as
//   active), which in turn puts "Offset Log Exposure to 0" at the true clip
//   point of the curve.
// - In Density Y mode with clamping enabled, the Y axis auto-scales to the
//   highest density within the active range; density grid uses 0.5 steps.
//
// v2.6 changes (on top of v2.5):
// - Margins now hug their content instead of scaling with the UI: the left
//   margin is sized to the widest Y label, the bottom to one row of X
//   labels, top/right only avoid clipping edge labels. Font and grid sizes
//   are unchanged; the wasted space at the left and bottom is gone. Works
//   across aspect ratios (16:9, 3:2, vertical).
//
// v2.5 changes (on top of v2.4):
// - "Offset Log Exposure to 0" now anchors the RIGHT end of the log exposure
//   axis at 0, counting down into negative values toward the left (exposure
//   relative to the top of the displayed range). Previously it anchored the
//   left end at 0. Note this option only affects the Log Exposure X axis
//   mode; it does nothing in Stops or Linear Input mode.
//
// v2.4 changes (on top of v2.3):
// - Stop ranges are now symmetric around mid gray (same stops above and
//   below), bounded by each encoding's clip point at code 1.0, capped at
//   +-10 stops. Pairs with probe v2.1, which also fixes the LogC4 formula
//   to the official ARRI spec (mid gray 0.278).
//   IMPORTANT: use with probe v2.1+ and keep Probe Encoding in sync.
//
// v2.3 changes (on top of v2.2):
// - Probe Encoding selector added (ARRI LogC3 / ARRI LogC4 / DaVinci
//   Intermediate). The probe strip now sweeps the full encodable range of
//   each transfer function (capped at 20 stops), so the display must know
//   which encoding the probe node is set to in order to label the X axis
//   correctly. IMPORTANT: keep this setting in sync with the probe DCTL
//   (v2.0 or newer).
//
// v2.2 changes (on top of v2.1):
// - "Clamp to Active Range" is back, enabled by default: the X axis zooms to
//   the stop range where the curve actually changes, trimming flat clipped
//   tails. Tuning knobs: ACTIVE_RANGE_* defines below.
//
// v2.1 changes (on top of v2.0):
// - "Datasheet Offset" replaced by "Offset Log Exposure to 0": shifts the
//   log exposure axis so it starts at 0 (datasheet-style relative log E).
// - Transparent background, enabled by default.
// - Chart Height slider removed. Chart Size defaults to Fullscreen and the
//   overlay mode is now a right-side overlay with a fixed width
//   (CHART_OVERLAY_WIDTH_PCT below).
// - The v2.0 "UI Scale % = 280" look is the baked-in default (UI_BASE_SCALE);
//   the slider is gone. Line Thickness defaults to 2.4.
// - The yellow vertical line marks mid gray (18% input / 0 stops). It is now
//   drawn at the exact mid gray position in every X axis mode instead of
//   relying on a grid tick landing there.

#define X_MODE_STOPS 0
#define X_MODE_LOG_EXPOSURE 1
#define X_MODE_LINEAR 2

#define Y_MODE_PERCENT 0
#define Y_MODE_DENSITY 1
#define Y_MODE_LINEAR 2

#define EOTF_NONE 0
#define EOTF_G24 1
#define EOTF_SRGB 2

#define CHART_FULLSCREEN 0
#define CHART_RIGHT 1

#define PLOT_FILL 0
#define PLOT_SQUARE 1
#define PLOT_ISO 2

#define PROBE_MID_GRAY 0.18f
#define PROBE_SAMPLE_ROW_OFFSET 0
#define PROBE_PRESENCE_THRESHOLD 0.05f

#define ENCODING_LOGC3 0
#define ENCODING_LOGC4 1
#define ENCODING_DI 2

// Stop range of the probe strip for each encoding, relative to 18% mid gray:
// symmetric around mid gray, bounded by the encoding's clip point at code
// 1.0, capped at +-10 stops. Must match the probe DCTL (v2.1+).
#define STOPS_LOGC3_MIN -8.2574f
#define STOPS_LOGC3_MAX 8.2574f
#define STOPS_LOGC4_MIN -10.0f
#define STOPS_LOGC4_MAX 10.0f
#define STOPS_DI_MIN -9.1178f
#define STOPS_DI_MAX 9.1178f

// Width of the chart in Right Overlay mode, as a percentage of frame width.
#define CHART_OVERLAY_WIDTH_PCT 40.0f

// Active range detection (ported from Sensitometry Curve Display): the probe
// strip is scanned in density space; a channel counts as "active" once its
// density deviates from its plateau value by more than the relative
// threshold (a fraction of that channel's full density range). The widest
// union across R/G/B wins. The result never collapses below the minimum span.
// Shadows and highlights use separate thresholds: the highlight shoulder
// converges much more slowly in density terms, so it needs a finer threshold
// to avoid being trimmed while the curve is still visibly rising.
#define ACTIVE_SCAN_SAMPLES 64
#define ACTIVE_RANGE_THRESH_SHADOWS 0.02f
#define ACTIVE_RANGE_THRESH_HIGHLIGHTS 0.005f
#define ACTIVE_RANGE_MIN_SPAN_STOPS 1.0f
#define DENSITY_EPS 1.0e-5f

// Thickness factor of the RGB curve lines (the Grid Thickness slider does
// not affect them).
#define CURVE_THICKNESS_FACTOR 2.4f

// UI auto-scaling: sizes are proportional to the chart's smaller dimension,
// referenced to a 1080px fullscreen chart. UI_BASE_SCALE bakes in the overall
// look (equivalent to "UI Scale % = 280" in v2.0).
#define UI_REFERENCE_HEIGHT 1080.0f
#define UI_BASE_SCALE 2.8f
#define UI_SCALE_MIN 0.55f
#define UI_SCALE_MAX 4.0f

// clang-format off
DEFINE_UI_PARAMS(x_mode, X Axis, DCTLUI_COMBO_BOX, 1, {X_MODE_STOPS, X_MODE_LOG_EXPOSURE}, {Stops, Log Exposure})
DEFINE_UI_PARAMS(y_mode, Y Axis, DCTLUI_COMBO_BOX, 0, {Y_MODE_PERCENT, Y_MODE_DENSITY}, {Output %, Density})
DEFINE_UI_PARAMS(output_eotf, Output Signal, DCTLUI_COMBO_BOX, 0, {EOTF_NONE, EOTF_G24, EOTF_SRGB}, {None / Linear, Video Gamma 2.4, sRGB Monitor})
DEFINE_UI_PARAMS(encoding, Probe Encoding, DCTLUI_COMBO_BOX, 0, {ENCODING_LOGC3, ENCODING_LOGC4, ENCODING_DI}, {ARRI LogC3, ARRI LogC4, DaVinci Intermediate})
DEFINE_UI_PARAMS(chart_size, Chart Size, DCTLUI_COMBO_BOX, 0, {CHART_FULLSCREEN, CHART_RIGHT}, {Fullscreen, Right Overlay})
DEFINE_UI_PARAMS(plot_shape, Plot Shape, DCTLUI_COMBO_BOX, 0, {PLOT_FILL, PLOT_SQUARE, PLOT_ISO}, {Fill Width, Square, Datasheet 1:1})
DEFINE_UI_PARAMS(grid_thickness, Grid Thickness, DCTLUI_SLIDER_FLOAT, 2.2, 1.0, 8.0, 0.2)
DEFINE_UI_PARAMS(show_grid, Show Grid, DCTLUI_CHECK_BOX, 1)
DEFINE_UI_PARAMS(clamp_active_range, Clamp to Active Range, DCTLUI_CHECK_BOX, 1)
DEFINE_UI_PARAMS(transparent_bg, Transparent Background, DCTLUI_CHECK_BOX, 1)
DEFINE_UI_PARAMS(offset_log_to_zero, Offset Exposure to 0, DCTLUI_CHECK_BOX, 0)

DEFINE_UI_TOOLTIP(X Axis, "X axis units: camera stops or log10 exposure. Both are relative to 18% mid gray (the yellow line) - same math, different labels.")
DEFINE_UI_TOOLTIP(Y Axis, "Y axis: output signal in percent, or density (-log10 of the output light).")
DEFINE_UI_TOOLTIP(Output Signal, "What your node chain outputs. Density measures light, so pick your output gamma to get photometrically true density values and slopes. None / Linear reads the code values as-is.")
DEFINE_UI_TOOLTIP(Probe Encoding, "Must match the Probe Encoding set on the probe node. Determines the stop range the strip covers.")
DEFINE_UI_TOOLTIP(Chart Size, "Fullscreen chart, or a fixed square chart on the right with the whole frame scaled down next to it.")
DEFINE_UI_TOOLTIP(Plot Shape, "Fill Width uses all available space. Square keeps a fixed square. Datasheet 1:1 sizes the plot so one density unit equals one log-exposure decade - slopes read as true gamma, like a Kodak datasheet (needs the Density Y axis).")
DEFINE_UI_TOOLTIP(Grid Thickness, "Thickness of the grid lines (the border is twice as thick). The RGB curves have a fixed thickness.")
DEFINE_UI_TOOLTIP(Show Grid, "Show the interior grid lines. The border, mid gray line, numbers and legends always stay.")
DEFINE_UI_TOOLTIP(Clamp to Active Range, "Zoom the X axis to the range where the curve actually changes, trimming the flat clipped tails.")
DEFINE_UI_TOOLTIP(Transparent Background, "Show the image behind the chart instead of a solid dark background (Fullscreen only).")
DEFINE_UI_TOOLTIP(Offset Exposure to 0, "Relabel the X axis to end at 0 and count down, so the leftmost number reads the total dynamic range directly. Pure relabeling - nothing moves.")
// clang-format on

